ent-ClothingOuterHardsuitNexusWorker = NSC-HRD-W1
    .desc = BingCo shipyard worker hardsuit. Offers barely more protection than none, but advanced servos let workers run fast with almost no movement penalty.
ent-ClothingHeadHelmetHardsuitNexusWorker = NSC-HRD-W1-H
    .desc = A simple worker helmet. Slightly less protective than a fully sealed suit.

ent-ClothingOuterHardsuitNexusMilT1 = NSC-HRD-M1
    .desc = Light combat hardsuit produced under Nexus patronage. Blueprints were purchased from a former Avantgarde supplier. This model is lightweight but not highly armored.
ent-ClothingHeadHelmetHardsuitNexusMilT1 = NSC-HRD-M1-H
    .desc = Light combat helmet with built-in night vision.

ent-ClothingOuterHardsuitNexusMilT2 = NSC-HRD-M2
    .desc = Medium combat hardsuit produced under Nexus patronage. Blueprints were purchased from a former Avantgarde supplier. Adequate armor but not very mobile. A rework of an older MOD suit design.
ent-ClothingHeadHelmetHardsuitNexusMilT2 = NSC-HRD-M2-H
    .desc = Medium combat helmet with built-in night vision and thermal imaging.

ent-ClothingOuterHardsuitNexusMilT3 = NSC-HRD-M3
    .desc = Heavy combat hardsuit produced under Nexus patronage. Blueprints were purchased from a former Avantgarde supplier. Trades some of M2's armor emphasis for a built-in shield generator.
ent-ClothingHeadHelmetHardsuitNexusMilT3 = NSC-HRD-M3-H
    .desc = Heavy combat helmet with built-in night vision and thermal imaging.

ent-DisciplinesDiskNSC = NSC technology disk
    .desc = R&D server disk with Nexus Star Consortium research disciplines.
